Cells. Human Burkitt lymphoma B cell line (BJAB) was used in this study. BJAB cells were propagated in phenol red-free RPMI medium (Invitrogen, Carlsbad, CA) containing 10% charcoal-stripped fetal bovine serum (FBS; Atlanta Biologicals, Lawrenceville, GA), L-glutamine, and antibiotics 40 . The cells used in this study were negative for mycoplasma as tested by Mycoplasma PCR ELISA (Roche Life Science, Indianapolis, IN). 


